---
description: Benchmark discipline and anti-overfitting rules for tests and evaluation
globs: tests/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---
Kobayashi must generalize across many fight types.

Rules:
- Never treat one imported fight log as sufficient proof of correctness.
- Any simulator accuracy improvement should be evaluated against benchmark cases, not a single fight.
- Favor changes that improve multiple benchmark families.
- Treat single-case gains as suspicious until validated more broadly.
- Do not bake benchmark-specific constants or one-off logic into the simulator.
- Preserve train, validation, and holdout separation if those datasets exist.

When proposing or validating a fix, include:
- the mismatch observed,
- the mechanic hypothesis,
- the expected affected fight families,
- the overfitting risk,
- the tests or benchmark slices that should change.
